\mathcal{N}(\mu,\sigma^2)
Var(x|x>a)=\sigma^2(1-\delta (\alpha))
\alpha=\frac{a-\mu}{\sigma}
\delta (\alpha)=\lambda (\alpha) [\lambda (\alpha)-\alpha], \,\,\, where \,\,\,  0<\delta (\alpha)<1
\lambda (\alpha)=\frac{\phi(\alpha)}{1-\Phi(\alpha)}
\frac{d Var(x|x>\alpha)}{d\alpha}=\lambda[(\lambda−\alpha)^2+\lambda(\lambda−\alpha)−1]
